{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# House Prices - Fase 2: Tratamento de Dados",
    "",
    "**IMPORTANTE:** O tratamento deve ser aplicado CONJUNTAMENTE no train e test.",
    "O test.csv do Kaggle NÃO tem SalePrice — é justamente isso que precisamos prever.",
    "O modelo deve receber dados tratados tanto no treino quanto na previsão.",
    "",
    "**Fluxo correto:**",
    "1. Carregar train.csv e test.csv originais",
    "2. Separar o target (SalePrice) do train",
    "3. Combinar train + test para tratamento conjunto",
    "4. Aplicar tratamento (missing, encoding, feature engineering)",
    "5. Separar de volta em train_clean e test_clean",
    "6. Treinar modelo com train_clean",
    "7. Prever com test_clean",
    "8. Enviar submission.csv pro Kaggle"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Importar bibliotecas",
    "import pandas as pd",
    "import numpy as np",
    "import matplotlib",
    "matplotlib.use('Agg')",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt",
    "import seaborn as sns",
    "import os",
    "import json",
    "",
    "sns.set_style('whitegrid')",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10, 6)",
    "plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 12",
    "",
    "DATA_DIR = '../data'",
    "REPORTS_DIR = '../reports'",
    "os.makedirs(REPORTS_DIR, exist_ok=True)",
    "",
    "print('Bibliotecas importadas!')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 0. Carregar Dados Originais",
    "",
    "**NUNCA use test_clean.csv como input!**",
    "O test_clean.csv é gerado APÓS o tratamento conjunto.",
    "O Kaggle vai te dar um test.csv sujo — seu pipeline deve limpá-lo."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Carregar dados ORIGINAIS",
    "train_raw = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, 'train.csv'))",
    "test_raw = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, 'test.csv'))",
    "",
    "print(f'Train: {train_raw.shape[0]} linhas x {train_raw.shape[1]} colunas')",
    "print(f'Test:  {test_raw.shape[0]} linhas x {test_raw.shape[1]} colunas')",
    "print(f'\\nColunas no train: {list(train_raw.columns[:10])}...')",
    "print(f'Colunas no test:  {list(test_raw.columns[:10])}...')",
    "",
    "# Verificar que test NÃO tem SalePrice",
    "print(f'\\nSalePrice no train: {\"SalePrice\" in train_raw.columns}')",
    "print(f'SalePrice no test:  {\"SalePrice\" in test_raw.columns}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Separar Target e Combinar",
    "",
    "**Por que combinar?**",
    "Para garantir que o tratamento seja IDÊNTICO nos dois datasets.",
    "Se tratarmos separadamente, podemos ter colunas diferentes (ex: One-Hot Encoding pode criar colunas diferentes se os datasets tiverem categorias diferentes)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Separar target do train",
    "y_train = train_raw['SalePrice'].copy()",
    "X_train = train_raw.drop('SalePrice', axis=1).copy()",
    "",
    "# Guardar IDs do test (precisamos pra submissão)",
    "test_ids = test_raw['Id'].copy()",
    "",
    "# Combinar features (sem target)",
    "combined = pd.concat([X_train, test_raw], axis=0, ignore_index=True)",
    "",
    "print(f'Combined: {combined.shape[0]} linhas x {combined.shape[1]} colunas')",
    "print(f'  - Train portion: {len(X_train)} linhas')",
    "print(f'  - Test portion:  {len(test_raw)} linhas')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Tratar Valores Faltantes (Missing Values)",
    "",
    "**Regra:** Colunas com >80% missing → remover. Restante → preencher.",
    "O preenchimento é feito no dataset COMBINADO para garantir consistência."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Ver missing values",
    "missing = combined.isnull().sum()",
    "missing = missing[missing > 0].sort_values(ascending=False)",
    "missing_pct = (missing / len(combined) * 100).round(1)",
    "",
    "print('Colunas com valores faltantes:')",
    "for col in missing.index:",
    "    print(f'  {col:<25} {missing[col]:>6} ({missing_pct[col]:>5.1f}%)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Remover colunas com >80% missing",
    "high_missing = missing_pct[missing_pct > 80].index.tolist()",
    "print(f'Colunas removidas (>80% missing): {high_missing}')",
    "combined.drop(columns=high_missing, inplace=True)",
    "",
    "# Preencher numéricas com mediana",
    "num_cols = combined.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns",
    "for col in num_cols:",
    "    if combined[col].isnull().any():",
    "        median_val = combined[col].median()",
    "        combined[col] = combined[col].fillna(median_val)",
    "",
    "# Preencher categóricas com 'None'",
    "cat_cols = combined.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns",
    "for col in cat_cols:",
    "    if combined[col].isnull().any():",
    "        combined[col] = combined[col].fillna('None')",
    "",
    "print(f'Missing restantes: {combined.isnull().sum().sum()}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Feature Engineering",
    "",
    "Criar novas features a partir das existentes.",
    "Isso é feito ANTES do encoding para evitar criar features desnecessárias."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Criar novas features",
    "combined['TotalSF'] = combined['TotalBsmtSF'] + combined['1stFlrSF'] + combined['2ndFlrSF']",
    "combined['TotalBath'] = (combined['FullBath'] + 0.5 * combined['HalfBath'] +",
    "                         combined['BsmtFullBath'] + 0.5 * combined['BsmtHalfBath'])",
    "combined['HouseAge'] = combined['YrSold'] - combined['YearBuilt']",
    "combined['RemodAge'] = combined['YrSold'] - combined['YearRemodAdd']",
    "combined['HasPool'] = (combined['PoolArea'] > 0).astype(int)",
    "combined['HasGarage'] = (combined['GarageArea'] > 0).astype(int)",
    "",
    "print('Novas features criadas:')",
    "print('  TotalSF, TotalBath, HouseAge, RemodAge, HasPool, HasGarage')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Codificar Variáveis Categóricas",
    "",
    "**Label Encoding** para variáveis com ordem natural (qualidade, condição).",
    "**One-Hot Encoding** para variáveis sem ordem (bairro, tipo de casa).",
    "",
    "Isso é feito no dataset COMBINADO para garantir que train e test tenham as MESMAS colunas."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Label Encoding para variáveis ordinais",
    "ordinal_cols = {",
    "    'ExterQual': ['Po', 'Fa', 'TA', 'Gd', 'Ex'],",
    "    'ExterCond': ['Po', 'Fa', 'TA', 'Gd', 'Ex'],",
    "    'BsmtQual': ['None', 'Po', 'Fa', 'TA', 'Gd', 'Ex'],",
    "    'BsmtCond': ['None', 'Po', 'Fa', 'TA', 'Gd', 'Ex'],",
    "    'HeatingQC': ['Po', 'Fa', 'TA', 'Gd', 'Ex'],",
    "    'KitchenQual': ['Po', 'Fa', 'TA', 'Gd', 'Ex'],",
    "    'FireplaceQu': ['None', 'Po', 'Fa', 'TA', 'Gd', 'Ex'],",
    "    'GarageQual': ['None', 'Po', 'Fa', 'TA', 'Gd', 'Ex'],",
    "    'GarageCond': ['None', 'Po', 'Fa', 'TA', 'Gd', 'Ex'],",
    "}",
    "",
    "for col, order in ordinal_cols.items():",
    "    if col in combined.columns:",
n    "        mapping = {val: i for i, val in enumerate(order)}",
    "        combined[col] = combined[col].map(mapping).fillna(0).astype(int)",
    "",
    "print(f'Label Encoding aplicado a {len(ordinal_cols)} colunas')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# One-Hot Encoding para categóricas restantes",
    "cat_remaining = combined.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns.tolist()",
    "print(f'One-Hot Encoding para {len(cat_remaining)} colunas')",
    "",
    "combined = pd.get_dummies(combined, columns=cat_remaining, drop_first=True)",
    "",
    "print(f'\\nDataset após encoding: {combined.shape[0]} linhas x {combined.shape[1]} colunas')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Remover Outliers (Só do Train!)",
    "",
    "**IMPORTANTE:** Outliers são removidos APENAS do conjunto de treino.",
    "O test não tem SalePrice, então não podemos identificar outliers nele.",
    "E mesmo que pudéssemos, NÃO devemos remover — o modelo precisa prever TODOS os casos."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Separar de volta ANTES de remover outliers",
    "X_train_clean = combined.iloc[:len(X_train)].copy()",
    "X_test_clean = combined.iloc[len(X_train):].copy()",
    "",
    "# Adicionar SalePrice de volta no train (pra identificar outliers)",
    "X_train_clean['SalePrice'] = y_train.values",
    "",
    "# Remover outliers do TRAIN apenas",
    "before = len(X_train_clean)",
    "outlier_rules = [",
    "    ('GrLivArea', 4000, '>'),",
    "    ('LotArea', 100000, '>'),",
    "    ('TotalBsmtSF', 3000, '>'),",
    "]",
    "for col, threshold, direction in outlier_rules:",
    "    mask = X_train_clean[col] > threshold",
    "    count = mask.sum()",
    "    print(f'{col} > {threshold}: {count} outliers removidos')",
    "    X_train_clean = X_train_clean[~mask]",
    "",
    "X_train_clean = X_train_clean.reset_index(drop=True)",
    "print(f'\\nTrain: {before} -> {len(X_train_clean)} linhas ({before - len(X_train_clean)} removidos)')",
    "print(f'Test:   {len(X_test_clean)} linhas (NÃO removidos)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Log Transform no SalePrice (Só do Train!)",
    "",
    "O test NÃO tem SalePrice, então aplicamos log APENAS no target do treino.",
    "Na hora de prever, o modelo vai dar o resultado em log — precisamos converter de volta com `np.expm1()`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Aplicar log transform no SalePrice do train",
    "skew_before = X_train_clean['SalePrice'].skew()",
    "X_train_clean['SalePrice'] = np.log1p(X_train_clean['SalePrice'])",
    "skew_after = X_train_clean['SalePrice'].skew()",
    "",
    "print(f'Skew antes: {skew_before:.4f}')",
    "print(f'Skew depois: {skew_after:.4f}')",
    "print(f'Redução: {(1 - abs(skew_after)/abs(skew_before))*100:.1f}%')",
    "",
    "# Visualizar",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))",
    "axes[0].hist(np.expm1(X_train_clean['SalePrice']), bins=50, color='steelblue', edgecolor='white')",
    "axes[0].set_title(f'SalePrice Original\\nSkew: {skew_before:.2f}')",
    "axes[1].hist(X_train_clean['SalePrice'], bins=50, color='coral', edgecolor='white')",
    "axes[1].set_title(f'SalePrice após Log\\nSkew: {skew_after:.2f}')",
    "plt.tight_layout()",
    "plt.savefig(os.path.join(REPORTS_DIR, 'saleprice_log_transform.png'), dpi=150)",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Separar X e y Finais",
    "",
    "Agora separamos o target das features no train.",
    "O test já está pronto (sem SalePrice)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Separar X e y do train",
    "y_final = X_train_clean['SalePrice'].copy()",
    "X_final = X_train_clean.drop('SalePrice', axis=1).copy()",
    "",
    "# Test já está sem SalePrice",
    "X_test_final = X_test_clean.copy()",
    "",
    "# Verificar que têm as MESMAS colunas",
    "assert list(X_final.columns) == list(X_test_final.columns), 'Colunas diferentes!'",
    "",
    "print(f'X_train: {X_final.shape}')",
    "print(f'y_train: {y_final.shape}')",
    "print(f'X_test:  {X_test_final.shape}')",
    "print(f'\\nColunas idênticas: ✓')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Salvar Dados Limpos",
    "",
    "Salvamos os dados tratados para usar na Fase 3 (modelagem).",
    "O test_clean.csv é gerado aqui, mas no fluxo real do Kaggle ele seria gerado pelo pipeline."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Salvar",
    "X_final.to_csv(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, 'X_train_clean.csv'), index=False)",
    "y_final.to_csv(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, 'y_train_clean.csv'), index=False)",
    "X_test_final.to_csv(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, 'X_test_clean.csv'), index=False)",
    "",
    "# Salvar metadados",
    "metadata = {",
    "    'train_rows': len(X_final),",
    "    'test_rows': len(X_test_final),",
    "    'columns': X_final.shape[1],",
    "    'target_skew_before': round(float(skew_before), 4),",
    "    'target_skew_after': round(float(skew_after), 4),",
    "    'outliers_removed': before - len(X_train_clean),",
    "    'high_missing_removed': high_missing,",
    "    'new_features': ['TotalSF', 'TotalBath', 'HouseAge', 'RemodAge', 'HasPool', 'HasGarage'],",
    "}",
    "with open(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, 'metadata.json'), 'w') as f:",
    "    json.dump(metadata, f, indent=2)",
    "",
    "print('Dados salvos:')",
    "print('  data/X_train_clean.csv')",
    "print('  data/y_train_clean.csv')",
    "print('  data/X_test_clean.csv')",
    "print('  data/metadata.json')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Resumo e Próximos Passos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "print('=' * 60)",
    "print('RESUMO DA FASE 2')",
    "print('=' * 60)",
    "print(f''",
    "Pipeline de tratamento:",
    "1. Carregar train.csv e test.csv originais",
    "2. Separar target (SalePrice) do train",
    "3. Combinar train + test para tratamento conjunto",
    "4. Missing values: {len(high_missing)} colunas removidas, resto preenchido",
    "5. Feature engineering: 6 novas features",
    "6. Encoding: Label (9 colunas) + One-Hot ({len(cat_remaining)} colunas)",
    "7. Separar de volta em train e test",
    "8. Remover outliers: {before - len(X_train_clean)} linhas (SÓ do train)",
    "9. Log transform: skew {skew_before:.2f} -> {skew_after:.2f}",
    "",
    "Dataset final:",
n    "  X_train: {X_final.shape}",
    "  y_train: {y_final.shape}",
    "  X_test:  {X_test_final.shape}",
    "",
    "PROXIMOS PASSOS (Fase 3):",
    "- Treinar modelo baseline (Regressão Linear)",
    "- Treinar Random Forest",
    "- Comparar métricas (RMSE, R²)",
    "- Cross-validation",
    "- Gerar submission.csv",
    "''')"
   ]
  }
 ],
